<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul-General <persName type="from">Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Abstract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-12-17"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Rodgers reports that the United States court opened this day, and
                            requests that the department cable date of confirmation of the court
                            officials.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>